## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (Summary)
  - Company: id (UUID, PK), name, industry, businessModel, products, targetCustomer, website, goals, etc.
  - HealthScore: id (UUID, PK), companyId (FK to Company), date (timestamp), overall (number), financial (number), market (number), brandSocial (number), benchmarks (JSONB), notes (text)
  - ReportSnapshot: id (UUID, PK), analysisId (FK to HealthScore), name, content (JSON or text blocks), createdAt
- API Endpoints
  - POST /health-scores
  - GET /health-scores?companyId=&limit=&since=
  - GET /health-scores/{id}
  - PATCH /companies/{id}
  - GET /companies/{id}
  - POST /reports/snapshots
  - GET /reports/snapshots/{id}
  - GET /reports/{analysisId}
- Security
  - JWT/OAuth with roles: owner, editor, viewer
  - Server-side authorization checks for all endpoints
- Validation
  - Use schema validation (Zod/Yup) for request payloads
  - For API responses, validate shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Runtime Safety Rules (CRITICAL)
  - Supabase query results: const items = data ?? []
  - Guard array methods: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - React useState for arrays: useState<Type[]>([])
  - API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining for nested access
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- Validation and Data Handling Notes
  - Normalize all inputs; default missing numeric fields to 0 or null where appropriate
