=== EDGE FUNCTIONS & DATABASE MIGRATIONS (MANDATORY) ===

Even without a Supabase project connected, you MUST create the correct files when the task requires them:

EDGE FUNCTIONS - create supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts for:
- LLM/AI features (chat, completions, embeddings, vector search)
- Third-party API integrations (Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Incoming webhooks from external services
- Any server-only logic or logic that must not expose secrets to the client
- Any prompt that says "create edge function" or "add edge function"
File location: supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts
Import pattern: import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";
Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code.

DATABASE MIGRATIONS - create supabase/migrations/<YYYYMMDDHHmmss>_<description>.sql for:
- Every new database table, view, or enum mentioned in the task
- Every schema change (ALTER TABLE, new index, new policy, etc.)
- Any prompt that says "create migration" or describes a data model
Make migrations idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS / CREATE OR REPLACE). Include RLS policies.
Do NOT run "supabase db push" or execute SQL directly — only create the .sql files.

MANDATORY CHECKLIST - Before finishing, verify:
- [ ] Migration SQL file(s) created for every database table/schema change mentioned
- [ ] Edge Function file(s) created for every server-side/secrets feature mentioned
- [ ] TypeScript types created for every new database table

=== TASK ===
# Health Scoring Engine

## Overview
You are building PulseBoard — a Health Scoring Engine and companion UX for company health analysis. The system computes an overall Health Score plus sub-scores (financial, market, brand/social) using weighted rules and optional benchmarking against industry norms. It stores historical scores for trend analysis, provides a primary Company Detail workspace, a primary Dashboard workspace, and a full AI-generated Report Viewer. All data flows are authenticated and access-controlled. The solution must be robust to missing data, guard against null/undefined values, and follow the runtime safety rules described in the project guidelines.

---

## Components to Build

1) HealthScore Schema (Backend)
- Purpose: Persist computed health scores and breakdown per company for history and trend analysis.
- Core fields:
  - id: UUID, primary key
  - companyId: UUID, required, foreign key to Company
  - date: timestamp/date of the analysis, default now
  - overall: number, 0-100, required
  - financial: number, optional
  - market: number, optional
  - brandSocial: number, optional
  - benchmarks: JSONB or equivalent, optional (industry norms, if provided)
  - notes: text, optional (context for this score)
- Relationships:
  - belongs_to: Company (via companyId)
- Indexes:
  - (companyId, date) composite index for trend retrieval
- Validation/Defaults:
  - Ensure numeric scores clamp to 0-100
  - Use data ?? [] patterns on fetch; validate response shapes
- Constraints:
  - History should allow many scores per company over time

2) Company Detail Page (Frontend)
- Purpose: Primary and only company workspace showing profile summary, comprehensive health score breakdown, analysis history, and editable forms for profile, financials, market, and social data.
- UI Components:
  - ProfileSummaryCard: shows name, industry, stock/balance placeholders, homepage, last updated
  - HealthBreakdownPanel: shows overall score with stacked sub-scores (financial, market, brand/social), trend sparkline
  - AnalysisHistoryTimeline: list of HealthScore entries (date, overall, sub-scores)
  - EditableSection: ProfileForm (name, industry, business model, products/services, target customer, website, goals)
  - EditableSection: FinancialForm (monthly revenue, expenses, profit margin, cash, debt, CAC/LTV, customer concentration)
  - EditableSection: MarketForm (competitors, pricing, market trends, customer segments, opportunities, threats)
  - EditableSection: SocialForm (channels, followers, engagement, posting frequency, traffic, brand mentions)
  - SaveSnapshotPanel: ability to save the current combined inputs as a snapshot (for quick restore)
  - Validation states, required-field indicators, and inline help
  - EmptyState/NoData state if no company exists
- Interactions:
  - Live validation with sensible defaults; prevent submission with missing required fields
  - Autosave drafts per section? (optional) If implemented, ensure proper debounce and null-safety
  - “Generate Analysis” or “Refresh Health Score” button on the page
  - Timeline allows drilling into a specific HealthScore to view details
  - Access control: only the authorized user for the company can edit
- Data considerations:
  - All forms initialize with useState<Type[]>([]) for array-like fields; if fields are single objects, use useState<Type> with proper defaults
  - Guard all API results for null/undefined; e.g., data ?? []
  - Use optional chaining when reading nested API results
  - When rendering lists from API data, wrap with Array.isArray checks: (Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [])
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels, keyboard navigable, semantic headings

3) Dashboard Page (Frontend)
- Purpose: Primary workspace focused on the user’s single company. Health at-a-glance, latest analysis, quick actions, and guidance to improve completeness and run analyses.
- UI Components:
  - HeroHealthPanel: overall health score, quick glance at sub-scores, trend indicator
  - LatestAnalysisCard: summary of the most recent HealthScore with date; quick link to view full Report Viewer
  - QuickActionsPanel:
    - Create/Update Company
    - Run New Analysis (Generate Analysis)
    - Import data (if applicable)
    - Guidance to improve completeness (progress bars per data category)
  - CompletionGuidancePanel: shows missing fields with soft guidance; accessible on the dashboard
  - EmptyStateCTA: if no company exists, show CTA to set up the company
- Data considerations:
  - Fetch company by authenticated user; if none, show CTA
  - All lists guarded with (data ?? []) and Array.isArray checks
- Interactions:
  - One-click action to trigger analysis (calls backend to compute HealthScore using current data)
  - Navigate to Company Detail on selection
- Performance:
  - Prefetch latest HealthScore and last 5 analyses for quick rendering
  - Debounce heavy computations when user updates data

4) Report Viewer Page (Frontend)
- Purpose: Full AI-generated report for a single analysis: executive summary, SWOT, financial analysis, market analysis, social analysis, top risks, opportunities, and prioritized action plan
- UI Components:
  - ReportHeader: Company name, analysis date, filters
  - SectionBlock: Executive Summary (editable text blocks)
  - SWOTPanel: Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, Threats (editable text)
  - FinancialAnalysisPanel: metrics, graphs, insights
  - MarketAnalysisPanel: market trends, competitive landscape
  - SocialAnalysisPanel: social presence metrics, engagement, sentiment (simple charts)
  - RisksPanel: top risks with severity
  - OpportunitiesPanel: top opportunities
  - ActionPlanPanel: prioritized actions with status, owner, due date
  - EditableTextBlock: inline editing for sections; save snapshots
  - SnapshotManagement: Save, load, compare snapshots
  - ExportPanel: export to PDF/Print
- Data considerations:
  - The AI-generated content is stored as text blocks; allow edits and saving snapshots
  - Use null-safe renders; if a section is empty, show placeholder text
- Interactions:
  - Edit and Save for each block
  - Snapshot save and restore
  - PDF export with current view
- Validation:
  - Ensure all required fields in the report exist before export
- Accessibility:
  - Clear headings, logical reading order, keyboard shortcuts for saving

